items.title: Trump admin live updates: Trump cancels legal status for 900,000
items.description: The DHS revoked the parole status of those who used the CBP One App to obtain the status. The move puts over 900,000 migrants up for deportation.

items.title: Iran says US talks to be 'indirect' despite Trump 'direct' negotiations announcement
items.description: Iranian officials confirmed Monday that Tehran would hold "indirect" high level talks with U.S. representatives in Oman this weekend.

items.title: Trump tariffs live updates: Sec. Bessent tells ABC deals could come 'very quickly'
items.description: Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent on Tuesday morning told ABC News he thinks deals can be made with other nations as some tariff negotiations begin.

items.title: LIVE:  ABC News Live
items.description: 24/7 coverage of breaking news and live events

items.title: Trump admin tells prosecutors to ease up on crypto enforcement
items.description: The Trump administration is pulling back its enforcement of crypto regulations, disbanding a unit dedicated to cryptocurrency enforcement
